'''''Atalantë''''' is a [[Quenya]] word meaning "the downfallen", from the verb-root ''[[talat-]]''. It was the name given to [[Númenor]] after its [[Downfall of Númenor|Downfall]].<ref>{{S|Akallabeth}}</ref>  [[J.R.R. Tolkien|Tolkien]] called it "''a happy accident''", because it invokes the name ''[[wikipedia:Atlantis|Atlantis]]''.<ref>{{L|257}}</ref>

